getTRLine

TRLine getTRLine(java.lang.String dbName,
                 java.lang.String identifier1,
                 java.lang.String identifier2,
                 java.lang.String nbHits,
                 java.lang.String level)
Gets a TRLine which describes which (selected) sequence analysis features trigger the application of the current Site Rule.

Parameters:
dbName - Generally is the name of the sequence analysis feature database.
identifier1 - The feature name e.g. the unique identifier of the motif in the given database, which is generally an accession number.
identifier2 - A secondary identifier for the motif, which is generally an entry name, and which is empty (‘-’) in Site Rule.
nbHits - The expected number of hits to the motif. Obviously, the rule is only triggered if at least one hit is found. The default value is '1' for Site Rule.
level - The minimum level that a hit must have to trigger the rule. The default value is '0' for Site Rule.
Returns:
a TRLine which describes which (selected) sequ3ence analysis features trigger the application of the current Site Rule.

getFeatureCondition

FeatureCondition getFeatureCondition(int featureGroupNumber,
                                     java.lang.String conditionPattern)
Gets the condition gives constraints on the FT features.

Parameters:
featureGroupNumber - The feature group number.For the consistency of annotation, multiple features that should be applied either all together or not at all should be grouped within a ‘Group’, to constrain the common presence of all sites. This group can the be referenced by case statements, for instance in the relevant KW and CC lines that depend on the presence of the feature.
conditionPattern - The feature condition pattern. The ‘pattern’ is specified in the PROSITE pattern format with the addition that the character ‘*’ may be used to specify an unconstrained range, e.g. ‘C-x*-C’. The region of the sequence corresponding to the feature must exactly match this pattern.
Returns:
the condition gives constraints on the FT features.

getAnnotationSection

AnnotationSection getAnnotationSection(java.util.List<CaseBlock> caseBlocks,
                                       InternalCommentsBlock internalCommentsBlock)
Gets the Annotation section of this Site Rule, which includes all UniProtKB annotation lines that can be applied to a rule match. Additionally, there can be lines which indicate condition statements ('case', 'else case', 'else') and a line which indicates the motif or alignments, according to which the feature positions are calculated. The line order is the same as in UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot.

Parameters:
caseBlocks - A block of KW line(s), CC line(s) and Feature Table lines associated with a CaseCondition.
internalCommentsBlock - Internal comments associated with AnnotationSection.
Returns:
the AnnotationSection of the Site Rule.

getKingdomLine

KingdomLine getKingdomLine(java.lang.String kingdom,
                           java.lang.String kingdomSubTaxon,
                           java.util.List<java.lang.String> exceptTaxonomicGroups,
                           java.util.List<java.lang.String> completeProteomeNotInTaxCodes)
Gets the taxonomic classification composed of the kingdom, optionally followed by the name of a sub-taxon, to further limit the application of the Site Rule to any taxonomic level. Valid values for kingdom are: ‘Eukaryota’, ‘Bacteria’, ‘Archaea’, ‘Viruses’, ‘Bacteriophage’, ‘Plastid’ and ‘Mitochondrion’. The two latter values designate proteins encoded in the organelle genome but not proteins encoded in the nucleus and targeted to the organelle. If it has been assessed with certainty that a Site Rule is not represented in: A taxonomic group, its name may be indicated in the ‘except’ field. A complete proteome, its taxcode may be indicated in the ‘not in’ field.

Parameters:
kingdom - The kingdom name.
kingdomSubTaxon - The kindom sub-taxon.
exceptTaxonomicGroups - The list of taxonomic group names not belong to this Kingdom.
completeProteomeNotInTaxCodes - The list of taxcode for complete proteomes not belong to this Kingdom.
Returns:
the taxonomic classification.

Parameters:

relatedLine - The list of related Site Rule accession numbers. Default is "none";
scopeBlock - The Scope Block that lists the taxonomic classes in which a rule match may be found.
internalCommentsBlock - Internal comments associated with the Computing section.
Returns:
Computing section contrasts with the Annotation section in that the line identifiers are no longer restricted to 2 letters.
